FBIS4-60956 "drsov084_i_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-084 Daily Report 2 May 1994 CENTRAL ASIA Kazakhstan Fire at Thermoelectric Plant Brings Industry to Near Halt Fire at Thermoelectric Plant Brings Industry to Near Halt LD0205092694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0700 GMT 2 May 94 LD0205092694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] Southern Kazakhstan's biggest thermoelectric plant, the Chimkent Thermoelectric-3 Plant, has stopped working after the failure of one of the pumps caused the plant's cable network to burn out. It took about three hours to put out the fire. The accident has practically brought to a halt two industrial giants -- a tyre factory and an oil refinery. Work is under way to clear up the accident.
